snippet.textDisplay: I'm thinking it would run better on premium 91-93 octane. I don't remember the compression ratio on the Sonny 711 you have but if its less than 10:1 and your only running 6 psi (less than 10 psi) I would think a lot of your ignition problems would go away as well as improve engine response and tune ability. I have seen examples of more octane is not better (flame spread too slow, plug fouling, and hard to tune w/race gas). If your plan is to crank the boost up over 20 psi then your gonna need some race gas. If your going to stay around 10 psi or less then you should work on a pump gas tune.... Plus you can buy fuel anywhere.
snippet.textOriginal: I'm thinking it would run better on premium 91-93 octane. FREAKING AWESOME SUPER-SKIFF GUYS!!😱😱😱❤️❤️❤️✅✅✅...........The Man Named "FINNEGAN"!!!.........Are you Related to the Famous Creator of the "FINNEGAN PIN" .........Ya Know, the Guy whose Cousin Invented The Lubricant called "INNERSLICKEN"!.......LOL!.....Just had to make a Funny 😂 Guys!........

I thought that was a Modular Ford DOHC Engine at First Look!😉....(Either a 5.0 Coyote, or 5.4 Condor, or Maybe even one of those GREAT '13-'14 Trinity 5.8's From the Last Gen. SHELBY GT-500's!) Ya know, with the Plugs Going into the Top of the Boom 💥 Boom 💥 Chambers!........

Yeah, I'm a FORD 4 Valve DOHC Guy!.......As I have a 2014 "TRACK-PACK" "COYOTE 5.0's!" WITH THE UNDERRATED 419 HP!...Yep, One Of THE VERY Last Of The Older Generation STANGS. To Roll Off The Line.) ...Ya know, Before FORD Turned the Mustang into a "EURO-STANG"!...........

Again Though!.......Savage "Water-Whip".......Back in the Day, I had a Cool Glastron 160-V With a "LOUD AS HELL" 1975 Johnson 135 HP! (Yeah She was Rated For Max. 100 HP!😉😉.......Those Older 2 Stroke V-4's used to SCREAM LIKE BANSHEE's (Until the 1980's came along, and Put all that SOUND DEADENING CRAP Into the Covers, and Lower-Units themselves!......Then came VRO For no more SMOKING 2 Strokes😩....

NOTHING SOUNDED MEANER THAN A OLD '70's 2 Stroke Screaming at 6250 RPM's up on the Lake in New Hampshire! SURROUNDED BY MOUNTAINS ON ALL SIDES!.......I was able to Push Her To 68 MPH (With a speed Prop.) But those Older Glastrons WOULD GET REAL SQUIRMY Until they Came out with "Power-Trim" (Which my Grandma 👵 Sprung For in '77 Before I got Killed!).........Ahhh......Nothing Better than a FAST BOAT!!😍😍😍.......Heck Most Peeps don't Realize that 50 MPH on the Water 💦 FEELS LIKE 100 MPH on land!!😉🤣🤣........

Enjoy 😊 THAT BEAST OF A JET!!.....(Although I Myself would be SCARED 😳 as SHITE!......Running her With Open "HUFFERS" like that!......FORGET THE H2O (As That Would just COOL THOSE Chambers off!......I would be afraid 😳 of One of those "SNAILS" Sucking up a WHOLE GOOSE!......(OR LOON, If you were up NORTH Far Enough!!)......

Again! GREAT VIDEO!......Be Safe!

Sean.

snippet.textDisplay:
Mike, did you ascertain the cause of the injector failure?
Basically the engine has just been sitting around for 4 years, so did the residual fuel in the system varnish up the injectors? Your new ultrasonic cleaner should make short work of cleaning them
In the future maybe the best policy will be to maintain matched sets of injectors, with known metered flow rates. AT least that way if this problem manifests itself again you will be properly prepared.
